# SentinelOne Windows Agent Installation Guide

### 1. Agent requirements on Windows
| Group | Windows OS | Agent Version |
|:-------:|------------|:---------------:|
| A     | Windows 11/11 23H2/11 24H2 64-bit <br /><br /> Windows 10 64-bit <br /><br /> Windows 8.1 64-bit <br /><br /> Windows Server IoT 2019/2022/2025 <br /><br /> Server/Server Core 2025 <br /><br /> Server/Storage Server/Server Core 2022 64-bit <br /><br /> Server/Server Core 2019 64-bit <br /><br /> Server/Storage Server/Server Core 2016 64-bit <br /><br /> Server/Storage Server 2012 R2 64-bit | 24.x ~ higher <br />23.x ~ lower
| B     | Windows 10 32-bit <br /><br /> Windows 8.1 32-bit <br /><br /> Windows 8 32/64-bit <br /><br /> Windows 7 SP1 32/64-bit <br /><br /> POSReady 7 <br /><br /> Server/Storage Server/Server Core 2012 (not R2) 32/64-bit <br /><br /> Server 2008 R2 SP1 32/64-bit | 23.x ~ lower

*Group A installers use 64-bit architecture only. You cannot use Agent installers that use 32-bit architecture. <br />
For endpoints with a Windows OS in Group A, select only Agent installers that use 64-bit architecture.* <br /><br />

### 2. Required Microsoft Security Updates Per Operating System
| Windows OS | Required Microsoft Security Updates |
|------------|-------------------------------------|
| Windows 8.1 64-bit <br /><br /> Windows Server/Storage Server 2012 R2 | KB2919442 <br /> KB2919355 (includes KB2932046, KB2959977, KB2937592, KB2938439, and KB2934018) <br /> KB3042058 to update the default TLS cipher suites. <br />
| Windows 8 <br /><br /> Windows Server/Storage Server/Server Core 2012 (not R2) | KB3003729 <br /> KB3042058 to update the default TLS cipher suites.
| Windows 7 SP1 <br /><br /> Windows Server 2008 R2 SP1 <br /><br /> POSReady 7 | KB2533623 <br /> KB2758857 <br /> KB4457144 <br /> KB3042058 to update the default TLS cipher suites. <br /> KB3140245 <br /> KB3020369 <br /> KB3033929 (SHA2) - This security update must be installed to meet the minimum requirements for the installer. |
<br />

<!-- - Please click for the installation file for each hotfix. <br /> -->

## 3. Minimum Hardware Requirements
| Minimum | Recommended |
|---------|-------------|
| 1 GHz CPU or better <br /><br /> Single-core (can install but there will be performance issues) | Dual-core |
| 1 GB RAM | 4 GB RAM or more |
| 2 GB free disk space on the Windows partition <br /><br /> 10% of disk for VSS snapshots (for each drive) | 10 GB recommended <br /><br /> 10% of disk for VSS snapshots (for each drive) |
<br />

## 4. Agent File Download
-  &nbsp;  **➊ Sentinels**  > **➋ PACKAGES** > **➌ All Platform Types** > **➍ Linux**
 ![alt text](./img/windows/image-13.png)
 ![alt text](./img/windows/image-15.png)
- Please download the latest **GA version**, which has been tested and stabilized. <br />
- The EA version is a test-only agent and may cause unexpected bugs or issues.
- Please download the ARM64 file if you are using an ARM CPU.

## 5. Check installation token
<!-- - &nbsp; **1) SENTINELS** > **2) SITE INFO** > **3) Site Token**
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-16.png) -->

- &nbsp; **1) SENTINELS** > **2) PACKAGES** > **3) Site Token**
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-17.png)
   *Must select a minimum **site scope to check** site token information.* <br />
   *ex) Global / 00_(KR)_PAGO Account / **Installation***

## 5. Agent Installation
- &nbsp; **1) SentinelInstaller.msi** > **2) Right Click** > **3) Install** <br />
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-6.png)
   * Installation is required with administrator privileges. <br />

- &nbsp; **1) Enter the Site Token** > **2) Install** <br />
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-8.png)

- &nbsp; Finish Click <br />
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-9.png)

## Agent Status Check
- &nbsp; Check the SentinelOne agent tray icon in the lower right corner - Click <br />
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-10.png)
- &nbsp; Check 'SECURE' and 'Online' status <br />
   ![alt text](./img/windows/image-11.png)
   *Agent checks are required if not in SECURE or Online.*

- &nbsp; AGENT DETAILS <br />
  ![alt text](./img/windows/image-18.png)
  *Can view information about the agent, such as the host name, agent version, and installation date.*

  